The Problem It Solves — Anchors the technical design in a real problem. Shows context for every architecture decision that follows.
How It Works — Request Lifecycle — A 9-step numbered walkthrough of exactly what happens from the moment an incident arrives to when the analyst gets a response. This is the most important section for technical interviews — it shows you understand the system end to end.
Architecture Diagram — Full ASCII diagram showing the Reasoning Controller's position in the stack, all surrounding components (MCP services, data layer, LLM endpoint, analyst dashboard), and which boundaries are public vs private.
MCP Microservices — Dedicated section for each MCP service (Logs, Inventory, Threat Intel) with actual endpoint designs and what each returns. Shows the controlled API pattern in practice.
AI Safety & Guardrails — Six named guardrails with implementation detail. This section alone signals serious product and engineering thinking around GenAI in a security context.
API Design — Real JSON request and response examples including the full reasoning output schema with evidence chain and prioritized recommended actions.
Deployment — Kubernetes config, environment variables, health check specs, and resilience patterns (retry, circuit breaker, fallback behavior).
Performance, Metrics, Security Model — The sections that round it out as a production-grade component README rather than a conceptual overview.

